artist's salon featuring choreographer performer and artist ann carlson events at stanford artist's salon featuring choreographer performer and artist ann carlson facebook twitter email print add to calendar our spring artist's salon features choreographer performer and conceptual artist ann carlson a guest artist at stanford university drama dept division of dance she will be speaking about her choreographic work both past and recent projects from the current baby play work for the very young spectator to the building performances with lawyers and animals ms carlson addresses locations of inspiration and defeat in the context of making live performance when wednesday april 20 2011 4 15 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where the clayman institute serra house 589 capistrano way stanford map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags lecture reading humanities drama visual dance arts sponsor clayman institute for gender research contact 725 0373 ann enthoven stanford edu admission free and open to all permalink http events stanford edu events 274 27493 more info last modified april 12 2011
